                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.105/50</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Mayer</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-28T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s November 16, 3 p.m. Haitian Government entirely disposed to make the
                    second modification, but desirous of effecting same by means of accord duly
                    signed rather than by an exchange of notes. If Legation’s suggestion to the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs to use latter method of modification, not adopted
                    by Haitian Government Legation will cable the Department requesting power to
                    sign an accord.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
